{"_id":"class-ranger","name":"Ranger","type":"class","img":"icons/svg/target.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Rangers are skilled stalkers and hunters at home in the wild. They choose a combat style (archery or two-weapon fighting), gain favored enemies, and eventually cast a small number of divine spells.</p><h3>Alignment</h3><p>Any.</p><h3>Key Class Features</h3><ul><li><strong>Favored Enemy:</strong> At 1st level choose a creature type; +2 on Bluff, Listen, Sense Motive, Spot, Survival vs. that type and on weapon damage. Additional favored enemies at 5th, 10th, 15th, 20th; bonus against one enemy increases by 2 at each interval.</li><li><strong>Track:</strong> Bonus feat.</li><li><strong>Wild Empathy:</strong> Improve animal attitude like a Diplomacy check (ranger level + Cha modifier).</li><li><strong>Combat Style (2nd):</strong> Archery (Rapid Shot) or two-weapon combat (Two-Weapon Fighting); improved at 6th and 11th. Benefits only in light or no armor.</li><li><strong>Animal Companion (4th):</strong> As druid, but effective druid level = half ranger level.</li><li><strong>Spells (4th):</strong> Prepare and cast divine spells from the ranger list; caster level = half ranger level.</li><li><strong>Woodland Stride (7th), Swift Tracker (8th), Evasion (9th), Camouflage (13th), Hide in Plain Sight (17th).</strong></li></ul>","hitDie":"d8","babProgression":"good","saves":{"fort":"good","ref":"good","will":"poor"},"skillPointsPerLevel":6,"classSkills":[{"key":"climb","name":"Climb"},{"key":"concentration","name":"Concentration"},{"key":"craft-alchemy","name":"Craft (Alchemy)"},{"key":"craft-armorsmithing","name":"Craft (Armorsmithing)"},{"key":"craft-bowmaking","name":"Craft (Bowmaking)"},{"key":"craft-weaponsmithing","name":"Craft (Weaponsmithing)"},{"key":"craft-trapmaking","name":"Craft (Trapsmithing)"},{"key":"handleAnimal","name":"Handle Animal"},{"key":"heal","name":"Heal"},{"key":"hide","name":"Hide"},{"key":"jump","name":"Jump"},{"key":"knowledge-dungeoneering